CELL SUSPENSION ID (Required): A unique ID for the biomaterial.
CELL SUSPENSION NAME: A short, descriptive name for the biomaterial that need not be unique.
CELL SUSPENSION DESCRIPTION: A general description of the biomaterial.
SOURCE TISSUE ID: The unique Tissue ID of the tissue this cell suspension was derived from.
GENUS SPECIES (Required): The name of the species to which the organism belongs.
SPECIES ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession
SPECIES ONTOLOGY LABEL: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field
ESTIMATED CELL COUNT: Total estimated number of cells in the suspension.
SELECTED CELL TYPE: The name of a cell type supplied by a user.
CELL TYPE ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession
CELL TYPE ONTOLOGY LABEL: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field
INSDC BIOMATERIAL ID: An International Nucleotide Sequence Database Collaboration (INSDC) sample accession.
DISSOCIATION PROTOCOL ID: An ID of a Dissociation protocol used to generate this cell suspension.
ENRICHMENT PROTOCOL ID: An ID of an Enrichment protocol used to generate this cell suspension.
CELL MORPHOLOGY: General description of the morphology of cells.
CELL SIZE: Size of cells in Cell size unit.
CELL SIZE UNIT: The name of a length unit being used.
LENGTH UNIT ONTOLOGY ID: An ontology term identifier in the form prefix:accession
LENGTH UNIT ONTOLOGY LABEL: The preferred label for the ontology term referred to in the ontology field. This may differ from the user-supplied value in the text field
SUPPLEMENTARY FILES: A list of filenames of biomaterial-level supplementary files.

SOURCE TISSUE ID: Use a Tissue ID you already provided in the Tissue Tab.

ESTIMATED CELL COUNT: Enter 1 for well-based assays. For example: 2100
SELECTED CELL TYPE: For example: bone marrow hematopoietic cell; cardiac muscle cell
CELL TYPE ONTOLOGY LABEL: For example: bone marrow hematopoietic cell; cardiac muscle cell
BIOSAMPLES ID: Enter ID if sample has been archived. ID can be from the DDBJ, NCBI, or EMBL-EBI and must start with SAMD, SAMN, or SAME, respectively. For example: SAMN00000000
INSDC BIOMATERIAL ID: Enter accession if sample has been archived. Accession can be from the DDBJ, NCBI, or EMBL-EBI and must start with DRS, SRS, or ERS, respecitvely. For example: SRS0000000
DISSOCIATION PROTOCOL ID: Use a Dissociation protocol ID you provided in the Dissociation protocol Tab.
ENRICHMENT PROTOCOL ID: Use an Enrichment protocol ID you provided in the Enrichment protocol Tab.
CELL MORPHOLOGY: For example: adherent cells; form single layer colonies
CELL SIZE: Enter a single value or a range. Average value is acceptable. For example: 15; 20-30
GENOTYPE: For example: DRB1 0401 protective allele; HLA-B*3901 allele
